runs.comm: full outside off stump, nice shape away, left alone by Masakadza
one is enough for a sighter. Bukhari pulls this one short and it's a bit wider as well. Masakadza murders it through cover-point for four
wide and swinging in the air, Masakadza throws his bat at it, and it catches an edge and scurries wide of slip  to the third man boundary
wide of off stump again, punched square. Raza wants a single but is sent back just in time as the throw comes in
scrambled single, but probably good running. Masakadza chops a shortish ball back onto his pads and the batsmen set off. Bukhari gives chase, picks up and throws at the stumps, but Raza is safe.
length ball on off stump, defended
length ball angled in on off stump, defended straight on the leg side
length ball about a foot outside off stump, Masakadza gets a huge stride in and defends towards the covers
down the track to a length ball outside off, bu he doesn't connect properly with a bit swing. Ball takes an under edge and it's fielded in the covers.
Gugten is keeping Masakadza honest. The batsman tried to step across and scoop it over his shoulder, but it was a proper short ball and it passed about a foot above him
wide yorker this time as Masakadza backs away. He throws his bat at it, but can't connect
again doesn't connect well, but at least it goes where he intends. Short ball, pulled straight of deep square leg, who runs around to keep it to two
length ball angled across the batsman. Raza opens the face and runs it down to the fence, perhaps a little finer than he imagined. That wasn't far from the keeper
length ball, closer into the stumps this time. Punched into the off side
shortish on off stump, Raza tries to open the face again but it's too close. It dribbles over to point
straighter, length ball, swung away towards deep midwicket
length ball on off stump, Masakadza defends awkwardly
full outside off stump, the batsman drives, but the ball stays low and goes under his shot
nicely delivered yorker on middle stump, dug out in the direction of square leg
length ball outside off stump. Masakadza drives on the up, but finds the fielder at cover
slower ball I think, length and on the pads. Masakadza aims a sweep, but he doesn't connect. Enough room in the infield to scamper a leg bye
a little bit of width and Raza frees his arms. That wasn't all that short, but the batsmen gets nicely under the shot, sending it over point for a boundary
responds with a good yorker that's jammed down on. Gets as far as mid off
length ball angled in to the stumps, Raza clips it to the legside sweeper for a single
good length ball on the pads, but perhaps he saw Raza coming and cramped him for room. Batsman bails out and defends

oh dear! You can't miss those opportunities when you're defending 140. A slightly slower ball draws a leading edge from Raza and the ball lobs high over mid on. The fielder backpeadals, pretty slowly, and doesn't really get close. Could have easily covered the ground. Batsman take two meanwhile

but it doesn't prove a costly miss. Malik fires one in on the pads again, and Raza hits at it too early, sending it high into the legside. The man at deep midwicket takes a few strides in and pouches it safely.
length ball on the stumps, cant' beat the infield
slowish length ball on the pads again, punched into the leg side
similar delivery on the legs, this time Masakadza finds a legside gap to get one
short-of-a-length ball on the body, defended
short ball, stuck in the pitch a little bit. Masakadza plays a controlled pull to the legside sweeper
length on the pads, turned away into a legside gap
down the leg side
fired down the leg side again, a little closer to the batsman this time
radar's all wrong. Still firing this down leg
goes a bit wide of the crease and bowls a length ball on the stumps. Masakadza gets a single to mid on
length ball on the pads, turned straight to square leg, but the fielder throws and hits the stumps, and the deflection allows a single
floated up on off stump, and Masakadza plays a muscular off drive, straight enough to beat the mid on fielder and all the way for four
short of a length just outside off stump, left alone
full on the stumps, Taylor clips it to leg but finds short midwicket
full on the pads, Taylor turns it behind square on the leg side and fine leg and deep square leg link up nicely to keep it to two
length on off stump, a thick inside edge squirts to square leg and there's a single on offer
yorker on off stump, Masakadza blocks it back to the bowler
full on off stump, driven far enough away from mid off to allow a single
on target straight up, a length ball on off stump. Masakadza defends
length outside off, Masakadza picks a big gap straight on the leg side and eases it there for a smart two
this one's a bit straighter, Masakadza turns it square on the leg side where the sweeper collects
on the pads again, and Taylor turns it to deep square leg for one
full, on off stump, driven to long on
floated up on middle, Taylor wihps it away to deep midwicket
darted in on middle stump, Taylor hits it back to the bowler
this one is flat and wide, driven away to long on
batsman winds up for a big shot, but doesn't go through with it. He hits a length ball back towards the bowler
full on the pads, Masakadza comes down the track and hits it into the gap straight of deep midwicket. A couple, but a direct hit might have had Taylor in trouble at the non-strikers' end
smart batting from Masakadza, gets a fullish one outside off and he hits it wide of long off for another two. Not trying to murder these.
length ball, batsman can't beat the offside field with a punch
but Taylor is not showing much of Masakadza's restraint. That's a floater on leg stump to start and Taylor gets low and wallops that way over deep midwicket for six
length ball on the off side, can't beat the field
full on the pads, maneuvred into a legside gap
boom. Full on the stumps, Masakadza swings the bat through it and the power in his shot has the ball sailing over the long on rope
tries to sweep, but they get a single off a deflection
length ball, punched to a fielder on the legside
full ball on the toes, turned away to fine leg
length on the legs, clipped away to fine leg again
short ball at the body, Masakadza tries to pull but gets it high on the bat. It loops away to square leg where there's noone there
short-of-a-length at the body, Taylor bunts this towards square leg and sprints through
yorker on leg stump, dug out to long on
length outside off stump, Taylor tries to glide this fine but short third man puts in a good dive and makes a valuable stop
full on the toes, knocked to long on for a single
slower short ball, outside off stump, Masakadza walks across and drags it somewhat aerially towards deep midwicket
fired in full at the stumps, Taylor opens the face and finds a gap in the cover region
attempted yorker, but Masakadza comes down the pitch, turns it into a full toss and whips it away to deep midwicket

quick single. Short ball outside off, a slower one i think, and though Taylor hits it straight to backward point, his partner wants a run. Taylor puts in a dive at the other end, but probably would have been ok
full on the pads again, worked to fine leg
slower ball to start, length on the stumps, Masakadza plays and expansive swipe but doesn't time it. Single to deep midwicket
Taylor makes a lot of room and tries to drive a full ball through the covers. It's fielded well, but they can't prevent a single
floated up on off stump, driven to long off
slower ball on the legs, turned around the corner to fine leg
full on leg stump, driven to long on
slower ball, length outside the off stump. Masakadza doesn't quite adjust for the lack of pace, but he lobs towards midwicket where there is a gap
length ball, Maskadza comes at him but doesn't get to the pitch. Still gets it into a legside gap though
this is length on the legs, again turned behind square on the legside for a single

gone! Can Netherlands take the initiative now? Masakadza charges again, but is completely done in by the lack of pace. He aims a big swing over long on, bit collects nothing but air. The ball slips under the bat and hits middle stump.
length ball angled in, and straightening. Chigumbura defends into the off side

double strike! This was full outside off stump, and perhaps asking to be hit, but Chigumbura slaps it straight to cover, who takes it above his head. Taylor becomse the key man now. It's still very much in either team's grasp.
short ball outside off stump, Williams swats this into a gap on the leg side and they take two
length, angled into off. Taylor just bunts it to the off side and takes a single
full on the stumps, driven to long on
floated up on the stumps, Taylor calmly clipping it into gaps, still. Hits this to deep midwicket
full on the legs, and Williams connects well with a flick, but there's a man at deep square leg. Four in the deep on the leg side
full on the legs, Taylor sweeps straight to fine leg
slower ball, angled across the leftie. Williams swipes at it and gets it wide of midwicket for one
good start. Almost a yorker on middle stump, Williams hits it back to the bowler
almost a yorker again, and Williams does slightly better, getting it wide of long on. They think abotu two but wisely decide against
Taylor makes room and throws his arm at another full ball on the stumps, and though he connects, it's straight to the man at extra cover
this is some good bowling. A full delivery again, Williams aims a big heave but can only manage an insde edge which goes to short fine leg
short of a length this time, still on the stumps. Another inside edge, another single
makes room and van Gugten misses his length slightly, delivering a low full toss. A thick outside edge carries the ball over point, but third man sprints around to keep it to two
shot! Taylor makes room, Van Beek overpitches slightly and Taylor lofts it powerfully over wide mid on for four

boom! Another one, Poor bowling, actually. It was a short slower ball outside the off stump, and Taylor reaches out to slap it past point for another four. All the men on the off side are saving a single
shortish and on the stumps, Taylor heaves it to the leg side
length ball on the pads, Williams clips it behind square to fine leg
full toss on the stumps, but Taylor is not too ambitious with that. Just backs away and strokes it to long off for one.
slogs away and finds the gap. This was short of a length from van Beek and Williams swung it away between deep midwicket and deep square leg. Big over for Zimbabwe.
length ball on the legs, Taylor just gently taps it to square leg and there's enough time for two,as the fielders have to run in from the fence
Wide down the leg side. Always a danger with this plan of stacking the boundaries on the on side
full on the toes, Taylor chips it to long on for a single
length ball outside off stump, Williams knocks it down to long off

so close to finding the man, but Taylor doesn't connect well enough. He slogs across the line as Malik sends down a length ball on the pads. Taylor gets it high on the bat and the advancing sweeper can't quite get there. Batsmen get two
full on the legs, Taylor places it well behind square on the leg side, so there's enough time for two
length on the stumps, Taylor keeps strike by blocking it into the off side and calling Williams through

he's got the big wicket! van der Gugten has been terrific in this match and he's delivered the wicket of the Zimababwe captain, with some help from Borren at cover. Taylor backed away and tried to lift it over the covers, but Borren leaps and pulls it down one-handed to breathe new life into his team's hopes.
full and wide, Sibanda gets on one knee and strokes it past cover for a quick couple
yorker again, driven to mid off for one
Williams backs away and van der Gugten follows him with the yorker, but he swats that away wristily in between deep square leg and deep midwicket
yorker again, but Williams digs it out well, wide of long on for another couple
yorker again, Williams gets an edge to it, but a diving Barresi can't stop it
yorker wide of off stump, Williams tries to slap it through cover but doesn't connect. There's an appeal for caught behind, but it's turned down.
full on off stump, Williams tonks that down the ground aerially, but Tom Cooper runs around to cut it off brilliantly
oh! What luck! Zimbabwe level the scores with the Frenchest of French cuts. Its full on the stumps, Williams swings away, and the inside edge evades Barresi and speeds to the rope. Scores tied.
full ball outside off stump, Williams fails to connect again and Netherlands keep hope

unnecessary from Williams, and this match is down to the last ball. It was a very,very good yorker on middle stump from Malik. Williams digs it out, but it goes straight to the bowler. The batsmen, however, have already determined that they would run, and Malik has the simplest of run outs to complete and the non-striker's end.

shot! SIBANDAAAA. Malik misses his length for once, sending down an overpitched ball. Sibanda gets low and wallops this high over long on for probably the biggest six of the match. The batsman high-five, Brendan Taylor watches on, almost stunned. The rest of the Zimbabwe team are going nuts.
